hey Steve, just a quick update - feeling about the same as yesterday, I’m going in to the surgeon at 3:40 today and will get the extraction at that time if the doctor thinks I need it.  I’ll let you guys know what’s going on - I don’t know if I’ll be able to come in for the assessment tomorrow if I do end up getting the surgery, but I definitely want to try at least doing it from home or something, if you guys are open to it.

hey man, was just going to message you guys.  I spoke with Adam and Frank before I took off yesterday, but not sure how much of this they already relayed to you. It turns out I’ve got an impacted wisdom tooth - normally they could just yank it, but the oral surgeon looked at my 2d x-ray and was concerned the tooth might be right on top of a nerve, which would complicate things.  I just got back from getting a CT scan at a different place, and am just waiting to hear from the surgeon - really hoping they can squeeze me in today, but I’m scheduled for tomorrow at 2:30, and it sounds like they won’t even be able to do the surgery at that time, as it’s just a ‘consultation’, and any surgery would have to go down at a separate appointment. 

 I’m in some serious pain right now and definitely can’t make it in today, but they threw me on antibiotics and gave me a saline rinse, so I’m hoping it’ll clear up and I’ll be able to come back in ASAP - I guess the pain is just from the infection, so if that clears up I should definitely be able to make it for Thursday and Friday, and can just put the surgery off.
